sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PatgB4HT
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Spider Silk Generator - 4x "B" Silk Construct with His Tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Silver Fusion assembly of basic parts
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Protein generator part for Spider Silk. Protein is a 4x fusion of spider silk "B" subunits, which were codon optimized to use a reduced set of tRNA codons (1 to 2 codons per amino acid). Contains a lactose/IPTG inducible , RBS, and a 10x-His tag for purification of protein.
IMPORTANT NOTE: This part uses Assembly Standard #23 (Silver Fusion) scar sites, which the sequence data below will not reflect (it shows Assembly Standard #10 scars).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Brian Smith

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K844000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 10x-Histidine tag with double stop codon TAATAA to allow for better extraction of tagged products and protein termination in a single part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kathleen Miller

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K844008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Spider Silk 1x Subunit "B" (Balanced tRNA codon optimized) with Met (ATG) added
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Created using mutagenesis PCR to add upstream Met (ATG) to part BBa_K844004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Spider silk subunit optimized to use a reduced set of tRNA codons (1 or 2 codons per amino acid); contains two elasticity domains and one strength domain, also contains 5??? Met (ATG) codon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrea Halling

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K844004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Spider Silk 1x Subunit "B" (Balanced tRNA codon optimized)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Artificially designed based on BBa_K844002 and DNA was synthesized
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Spider silk subunit optimized to use a more balanced, but still greatly reduced, number of tRNA codons; contains two elasticity domains and one strength domain.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrea Halling
